spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:description: PCI is a complex interface with a wide variety of uses in computer and embedded systems applications. CorePCIF AHB expands on the popular CorePCIF by adding an AHB slave interface allowing PCI interfaces to be automatically added to systems created in CoreConsole. CorePCIF AHB supports 32-Bit PCI and AHB buses with 33/66 MHz PCI operation in master, target, and master/target configurations. The master configuration includes a built-in DMA controller. CorePCIF AHB includes testbenchs for system verification
